74
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:47,120
I know that Cindy's death
must be hard for you to take.

75
00:06:47,960 --> 00:06:50,320
However, life still goes on.

76
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:51,800
You still have school tomorrow,

77
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:54,640
so rest early, all right?

78
00:06:56,680 --> 00:07:00,200
Why did God let such a cruel thing happen?

79
00:07:02,840 --> 00:07:04,760
Many things happen without good reason.

80
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:08,960
However, no matter what you face,

81
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:12,920
never be doubtful and never give up.

82
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:16,040
The intention conveyed by God

83
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:17,560
is one of peace…

84
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:20,120
and not one of disaster.

85
00:07:20,840 --> 00:07:22,760
How is this not a disaster?

86
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:26,800
How can human beings be so cruel…

87
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:28,640
and kill another person?

88
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:36,120
We must believe that
God has good intentions.

89
00:07:37,080 --> 00:07:40,320
How is death a good intention?

90
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:49,600
Death is not the end.

91
00:07:50,480 --> 00:07:53,600
It's the beginning of eternal life.

92
00:07:55,800 --> 00:07:57,280
It's just like…

93
00:07:57,360 --> 00:07:58,840
Although Mom has left us,

94
00:07:58,920 --> 00:08:01,720
