95
00:08:02,320 --> 00:08:03,760
We'll meet her again one day.

96
00:08:04,280 --> 00:08:07,280
Similarly, we'll meet Cindy again one day.

97
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:16,120
All right.

98
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:19,560
Hurry and finish the milk
and get some rest.

99
00:08:23,280 --> 00:08:24,520
Good night, Dad.

100
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:26,080
Good night.

101
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:58,360
Hey.

102
00:09:00,760 --> 00:09:02,560
It would be easier if you were still here.

103
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:06,600
You could be here for our daughter,

104
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:09,400
cry with her,

105
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:11,880
laugh with her,

106
00:09:12,920 --> 00:09:14,360
<i>talk with her about her problems,</i>

107
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:17,200
<i>sleep with her.</i>

108
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:23,520
<i>That way, she wouldn't be so lonely.</i>

109
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:29,880
<i>Our daughter needs you.</i>

110
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:37,080
Actually, I need you too.

111
00:09:41,280 --> 00:09:43,000
How's it like in Heaven?

112
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:48,200
How's life over there?

113
00:12:29,520 --> 00:12:32,760
A female university student calling
a private hire car to this hotel.

114
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:34,080
It's pretty telling.

115
00:12:34,160 --> 00:12:35,160
Telling of what?

116
00:12:35,240 --> 00:12:37,040
There's no evidence,
so stop spouting nonsense.

117
00:12:37,560 --> 00:12:39,000
High heels worth more than $1,000.

118
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:40,960
A single-parent family.
Her mother's a cleaner.

119
00:12:41,040 --> 00:12:42,200
Did money fall from the sky?

120
00:12:42,280 --> 00:12:44,440
- I couldn't bear to buy it for myself.
- Yours aren't cheap either.

121
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:45,840
Master.

122
00:12:45,920 --> 00:12:47,040
It seems like you took notice of me.

123
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:48,560
Are my new shoes nice?

124
00:12:48,640 --> 00:12:49,960
Who's your master?

125
00:12:50,040 --> 00:12:51,600
I don't take disciples.
Stop calling me that.

126
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:54,360
Yes, Master!

127
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:56,080
Check if there's
anything dirty on my back.

128
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:06,080
Sir, could you rewind it by two seconds?

129
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:07,120
Okay.

130
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:15,240
Check the time that they left.

131
00:13:24,120 --> 00:13:25,520
Do this.

132
00:13:26,280 --> 00:13:28,520
Check all the cars that left
the parking lot

133
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:30,680
at 11:00 a.m. on March 5

134
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:33,520
and all the private hire cars
that arrived at the hotel.

135
00:13:33,600 --> 00:13:35,640
We must find out who this man is.

136
00:13:36,160 --> 00:13:37,640
Do you have footage
from outside the hotel?

137
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:38,680
Yes.

138
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:56,720
The CCTV footage indicates that…

139
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:59,800
Cindy left from this road.

140
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:04,600
Why would a young girl come
to a back alley at such a late timing?

141
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:06,320
Even if she called for a private hire car,

142
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:08,280
she wouldn't have been waiting here.

143
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:11,080
There are two possibilities.

144
00:14:11,160 --> 00:14:13,240
One, someone picked her up.

145
00:14:13,760 --> 00:14:14,760
Two,

146
00:14:14,840 --> 00:14:17,560
she realized she was being followed
and tried to escape here.

147
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:18,560
We need evidence.

148
00:14:20,160 --> 00:14:21,080
Master,

149
00:14:21,160 --> 00:14:22,840
I've given it some serious thought.

150
00:14:22,920 --> 00:14:24,960
I don't think this was
the work of the Leap Day Killer.

151
00:14:25,040 --> 00:14:27,000
Firstly, she didn't die on a leap day.

152
00:14:27,080 --> 00:14:29,640
Secondly, the body was not dismembered.

153
00:14:32,240 --> 00:14:33,240
Master.

154
00:14:33,320 --> 00:14:34,640
Any thoughts?

155
00:14:35,840 --> 00:14:37,640
I know you think I'm very smart.

156
00:14:37,720 --> 00:14:39,880
Praise me, won't you? Don't be so stingy.

157
00:15:31,520 --> 00:15:32,560
Everyone…

158
00:15:33,440 --> 00:15:35,480
Today, on behalf of Cindy's family,

159
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:40,160
I would like to thank
her family and friends

160
00:15:40,240 --> 00:15:43,000
as well as our fellow brothers
and sisters in Christ

161
00:15:43,520 --> 00:15:46,480
for participating in her memorial service.

162
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:50,480
We're all saddened

163
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:52,320
by Cindy's sudden departure.

164
00:15:53,440 --> 00:15:56,120
We wonder why the murderer was so cruel.

165
00:15:58,200 --> 00:15:59,840
The rage and sense of injustice we have

166
00:15:59,920 --> 00:16:03,040
towards her murderer

167
00:16:04,720 --> 00:16:06,120
is completely understandable

168
00:16:07,760 --> 00:16:09,480
because we're only human.

169
00:16:12,720 --> 00:16:15,760
However, God wants us to be forgiving.

170
00:16:16,720 --> 00:16:18,080
We must learn to be forgiving.

171
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:21,720
That's because rage
and a sense of injustice

172
00:16:22,240 --> 00:16:24,200
will only make us increasingly unhappy.

173
00:16:25,560 --> 00:16:27,920
It's like ingesting poison every day.

174
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:31,480
We're the victims,

175
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:34,320
but we also become our own perpetrators.

176
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:04,560
I hate you.

177
00:17:07,720 --> 00:17:09,839
You caused my daughter to die.

178
00:17:14,319 --> 00:17:16,359
Like everyone else,

179
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:18,680
I hate your exhibition.

180
00:17:20,119 --> 00:17:23,280
You caused Cindy to be murdered!

181
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:38,880
However,

182
00:17:39,520 --> 00:17:41,560
that pastor told me…

183
00:17:43,520 --> 00:17:46,120
that you had nothing
to do with Cindy's death.

184
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:52,160
I'm so angry,

185
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:54,720
but I have no one to lash out at,

186
00:17:54,800 --> 00:17:56,720
so I cursed at you.

187
00:17:56,800 --> 00:17:58,240
I'm sorry.

188
00:17:58,840 --> 00:18:00,200
I'm sorry.

189
00:18:02,680 --> 00:18:04,480
I'm the one…

190
00:18:05,640 --> 00:18:07,120
who should apologize.

191
00:18:22,160 --> 00:18:25,280
I can understand how you feel now.

192
00:18:29,040 --> 00:18:30,160
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

193
00:19:05,840 --> 00:19:07,200
We met yesterday.

194
00:19:08,120 --> 00:19:09,760
Can I ask you some questions?

195
00:19:15,640 --> 00:19:16,960
Were you good friends?

196
00:19:20,760 --> 00:19:23,120
I'm the leader of Cindy's cell group.

197
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:29,440
Did Cindy display
any unusual behavior recently?

198
00:19:36,280 --> 00:19:39,240
When was the last time
you were in contact with her?

199
00:19:44,280 --> 00:19:46,360
It was around two weeks ago.

200
00:19:48,080 --> 00:19:50,000
I don't really remember.

201
00:19:52,240 --> 00:19:54,440
You can check your text messages.

202
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:58,760
We… usually…

203
00:19:59,720 --> 00:20:01,280
call each other.

204
00:20:04,040 --> 00:20:05,760
Do young people still call each other?

205
00:20:09,080 --> 00:20:10,800
The members of our church

206
00:20:11,320 --> 00:20:13,040
prefer to call each other.

207
00:20:15,680 --> 00:20:17,840
There are call records
for phone calls too.

208
00:20:24,120 --> 00:20:25,160
Do you…

209
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:28,800
wish to check my call records?

210
00:20:30,040 --> 00:20:31,240
I don't have to anymore.

211
00:20:32,080 --> 00:20:35,240
If you had anything to hide,
you would've already deleted it.

212
00:20:35,920 --> 00:20:36,880
Am I right?

213
00:20:44,680 --> 00:20:45,760
- Pastor.
- Hey.

214
00:20:45,840 --> 00:20:47,560
- Is anything wrong?
- Nothing's wrong.

215
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:50,520
My subordinate is just asking
some questions as a formality.

216
00:20:51,960 --> 00:20:53,360
It's tough for you policemen.

217
00:20:53,880 --> 00:20:54,880
You even have to come to a funeral.

218
00:20:55,520 --> 00:20:56,680
It's not easy.

219
00:20:56,760 --> 00:20:58,080
It's only right.

220
00:20:58,160 --> 00:21:00,320
We're giving
the family some moral support.

221
00:21:01,480 --> 00:21:04,000
Why didn't Cindy's father
attend the funeral?

222
00:21:05,240 --> 00:21:08,680
Her parents haven't been in contact
with each other since their divorce.

223
00:21:09,520 --> 00:21:11,720
She grew up in a single-parent family.

224
00:21:12,240 --> 00:21:14,200
It's inevitable that she had
some emotional trauma.

225
00:21:14,280 --> 00:21:15,160
She had a tough life.

226
00:21:16,360 --> 00:21:17,400
I share the same sentiment.

227
00:21:18,880 --> 00:21:22,040
It's indeed not easy for someone
who grew up in a single-parent family.

228
00:21:24,240 --> 00:21:25,280
It's not easy indeed.

229
00:21:32,880 --> 00:21:35,800
Regardless,
be careful whenever you're outside.

230
00:21:35,880 --> 00:21:38,160
Also, tell me wherever you're going.

231
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:42,480
If it's really the Leap Day Killer,

232
00:21:42,560 --> 00:21:44,120
he always targets young girls,

233
00:21:44,640 --> 00:21:46,600
girls around your age.

234
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:51,040
Zhang Tingting.

235
00:21:53,880 --> 00:21:55,840
Did you hear what I said?

236
00:22:01,040 --> 00:22:03,680
I know that Cindy's death
must have been hard on you.

237
00:22:04,440 --> 00:22:06,760
However, God will judge everyone.

238
00:22:07,440 --> 00:22:09,000
The murderer will be caught eventually.

239
00:22:15,880 --> 00:22:16,960
- Dad.
- Hmm?

240
00:22:18,600 --> 00:22:20,920
How does God treat liars?

241
00:22:23,400 --> 00:22:24,640
You should know that.

242
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:28,920
Will they really be forgiven?

243
00:22:31,160 --> 00:22:34,240
As long as they repent,
they'll be forgiven.

244
00:22:37,440 --> 00:22:39,600
How does one know that
they've been forgiven?

245
00:22:40,520 --> 00:22:44,000
Can one really tell… white lies?

246
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:48,560
White lies are still lies.

247
00:22:50,360 --> 00:22:52,160
What are you trying to tell me?

248
00:22:54,360 --> 00:22:55,560
It's nothing.

249
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:00,440
Something's definitely troubling you.

250
00:23:02,040 --> 00:23:04,000
Whatever it is, you can tell me.

251
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:11,120
Dad.

252
00:23:12,040 --> 00:23:14,360
I'm sorry, but I'm not in the mood to eat.

