The coroner's report indicates

271
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:26,760
sleeping pills were found
in both of their bodies.

272
00:25:26,840 --> 00:25:28,400
They were both dismembered.

273
00:25:29,040 --> 00:25:31,200
Sera's injuries were more prominent.

274
00:25:31,720 --> 00:25:32,680
As for Cindy…

275
00:25:32,760 --> 00:25:33,680
WHAT DO THESE 3 HAVE IN COMMON?

276
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:36,840
You'll share about Cindy's case.

277
00:25:36,920 --> 00:25:38,600
You presented a good analysis that day.

278
00:25:40,400 --> 00:25:42,320
I don't think Cindy was murdered
by the Leap Day Killer.

279
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:44,560
Firstly, she didn't die on a leap day.

280
00:25:44,640 --> 00:25:46,480
Secondly, she wasn't dismembered.

281
00:25:47,000 --> 00:25:48,840
Perhaps, the killer
didn't have time to do so.

282
00:25:48,920 --> 00:25:49,960
Sir.

283
00:25:50,880 --> 00:25:53,040
These are Cindy's call records.

284
00:25:56,280 --> 00:25:58,400
She called Zhang Tingting…

285
00:25:59,240 --> 00:26:01,760
and someone called Sun Shanwen.

286
00:26:04,360 --> 00:26:06,000
She's definitely lying.

287
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:14,200
It's okay.

288
00:26:14,280 --> 00:26:15,800
Relax. Treat this as a chit-chat.

289
00:26:17,920 --> 00:26:21,840
Are you certain that the last time
you contacted Cindy was two weeks ago?

290
00:26:30,320 --> 00:26:32,800
However, Cindy's call records
indicate that

291
00:26:32,880 --> 00:26:37,000
she called you at 12:55 a.m.
on the night she died.

292
00:26:39,680 --> 00:26:40,840
Tingting…

293
00:26:43,920 --> 00:26:45,880
it's against the law to falsify evidence.

294
00:26:49,640 --> 00:26:50,600
Tingting,

295
00:26:51,280 --> 00:26:52,880
be honest with the police.

296
00:26:52,960 --> 00:26:55,360
Otherwise, there will be
serious consequences.

297
00:26:59,040 --> 00:27:00,160
Dad.

298
00:27:01,400 --> 00:27:02,680
Why was Cindy looking for you?

299
00:27:07,680 --> 00:27:09,040
She borrowed money from me.

300
00:27:11,720 --> 00:27:13,920
So, how much did she borrow?

301
00:27:16,360 --> 00:27:17,760
She borrowed $500.

302
00:27:20,040 --> 00:27:21,240
Did you lend it to her?

303
00:27:28,840 --> 00:27:30,840
I've finished counting these.
The total is $900.

304
00:27:30,920 --> 00:27:32,120
I have something to do,
so I'll leave first.

305
00:27:32,200 --> 00:27:34,040
- Okay. Bye! Thanks!
- Okay. Bye.

306
00:27:57,480 --> 00:27:58,920
Dear God,

307
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:01,640
you taught us to love and help others.

308
00:28:01,720 --> 00:28:05,760
We shouldn't leave our friends
in the lurch if they're in trouble, right?

309
00:28:06,960 --> 00:28:08,760
The money belongs to you.

310
00:28:08,840 --> 00:28:12,600
However,
if I take some first to help Cindy,

311
00:28:13,120 --> 00:28:15,880
you won't be angry at me, right?

312
00:28:16,680 --> 00:28:19,080
Cindy, this really is the last time.

313
00:28:19,160 --> 00:28:21,280
Last time, you said
you broke your classmate's laptop.

314
00:28:21,360 --> 00:28:24,200
This time, your classmate's mother
is dying soon.

315
00:28:24,280 --> 00:28:26,640
What's next?

316
00:28:27,360 --> 00:28:28,960
You won't lie to me, right?

317
00:28:29,040 --> 00:28:30,600
It's all true!

318
00:28:30,680 --> 00:28:33,800
I swear I'll die a tragic death
if I'm lying to you, all right?

319
00:28:34,560 --> 00:28:36,240
Why make it so serious?

320
00:28:37,160 --> 00:28:38,400
I believe you.

321
00:28:41,000 --> 00:28:42,720
Remember not to tell anyone.

322
00:28:42,800 --> 00:28:45,320
I'll give it back to the church
once I have the money.

323
00:28:45,400 --> 00:28:47,600
She swore to me!

324
00:28:47,680 --> 00:28:50,520
She swore that she would die
a tragic death if she was lying to me.

325
00:28:51,160 --> 00:28:53,720
Did I cause her death?

326
00:28:53,800 --> 00:28:55,760
Don't believe such things like swearing.

327
00:28:55,840 --> 00:28:56,880
Everything's fine.

328
00:28:58,280 --> 00:28:59,920
I'm sorry. I'll continue.

329
00:29:00,440 --> 00:29:01,480
Okay.

330
00:29:04,920 --> 00:29:07,560
When Cindy called you on the day she died,
what did she say?

331
00:29:10,720 --> 00:29:13,760
She asked me for the number
of our classmate, Shanwen.

332
00:29:17,080 --> 00:29:18,600
Why was Cindy looking for him?

333
00:29:20,640 --> 00:29:23,960
I asked her,
but she didn't tell me the reason.

334
00:29:28,640 --> 00:29:30,440
Is there anything else
you're hiding from us?

335
00:29:31,040 --> 00:29:33,000
There's nothing else! I swear!

336
00:29:38,280 --> 00:29:39,520
I've recorded it all down.

337
00:29:41,160 --> 00:29:42,480
Thank you for your cooperation.

338
00:29:42,560 --> 00:29:43,840
Sorry to disturb you, Pastor.

339
00:29:54,960 --> 00:29:55,960
Safe travels.

340
00:30:14,240 --> 00:30:15,200
You.

341
00:30:16,120 --> 00:30:17,720
What have I always taught you?

342
00:30:22,400 --> 00:30:24,680
I'll put back the money that you took
from the tithe offering bag.

343
00:30:25,440 --> 00:30:28,320
I'll report this to the committee, and
we'll see how they want to handle this.

344
00:30:31,800 --> 00:30:33,720
I'm sorry, Dad.

345
00:30:35,920 --> 00:30:37,440
It's all right as long as you repent.

346
00:30:38,120 --> 00:30:39,960
All right. Stop crying.

347
00:30:41,320 --> 00:30:42,760
All right. Good girl.

348
00:30:43,280 --> 00:30:45,320
There are no secrets between us.
All right?

349
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:50,760
There won't be
any secrets between us any longer.

350
00:30:55,040 --> 00:30:58,440
Why would she ask for a guy's number
in the middle of the night?

351
00:30:58,520 --> 00:31:00,560
Sun Shanwen.

352
00:31:01,080 --> 00:31:02,600
He's Sera's younger brother.

353
00:31:04,280 --> 00:31:05,480
Let's go to his place now!

354
00:31:49,200 --> 00:31:51,240
Hey! Are you waiting for an invitation?

355
00:32:00,800 --> 00:32:02,040
What are you waiting for then?

356
00:32:03,800 --> 00:32:07,280
A murder case
makes life hell for the living.

357
00:32:18,240 --> 00:32:19,720
Do you have an update about the murderer?

358
00:32:22,200 --> 00:32:24,120
Your son is related to a murder case.

359
00:32:24,200 --> 00:32:26,240
We wish to speak with him.

360
00:32:27,120 --> 00:32:28,640
What do you mean?

361
00:32:28,720 --> 00:32:29,880
You're not handling my daughter's case,

362
00:32:29,960 --> 00:32:31,480
and now you're making accusations
about my son?

363
00:32:32,360 --> 00:32:36,200
Your son was the last person
whom the deceased, Cindy Lau, called.

364
00:32:36,280 --> 00:32:37,600
I'm sure you've made a mistake.

365
00:32:37,680 --> 00:32:39,440
My son doesn't know anyone named Cindy.

366
00:32:39,520 --> 00:32:40,920
Call…

367
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:42,160
Give me the call records.

368
00:32:44,840 --> 00:32:46,280
The call records indicate that,

369
00:32:46,800 --> 00:32:49,560
at 12:59 a.m. on March 5,

370
00:32:49,640 --> 00:32:50,960
they were on a call with each other.

371
00:32:52,360 --> 00:32:53,640
I'll be straight with you.

372
00:32:53,720 --> 00:32:56,760
The coroner's report indicated there were
traces of semen in Cindy's body.

373
00:32:56,840 --> 00:32:58,920
We're currently figuring out
this man's identity.

374
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:01,320
There's a possibility that
he could be your son.

375
00:33:01,400 --> 00:33:03,000
We need him to come in for a test.

376
00:33:03,520 --> 00:33:04,640
I'm calling my lawyer.

377
00:33:05,240 --> 00:33:06,720
You can test all you want.

378
00:33:06,800 --> 00:33:07,960
I'm not scared of you.

379
00:33:27,880 --> 00:33:30,360
I'll be in touch again
when the report is out.

380
00:33:32,360 --> 00:33:33,840
I hadn't even finished my sentence.

381
00:33:34,520 --> 00:33:35,560
Thank you.

382
00:33:37,840 --> 00:33:38,680
Don't worry.

383
00:33:39,280 --> 00:33:41,680
The evidence will speak for itself,
even if they don't.

384
00:33:42,560 --> 00:33:44,520
Shanwen. Shanwen!

385
00:33:44,600 --> 00:33:46,280
Why did Cindy look for you?

386
00:33:46,920 --> 00:33:48,360
What did you tell the police?

387
00:33:49,720 --> 00:33:52,080
What must I do to make you speak up?

388
00:33:52,920 --> 00:33:54,400
- Must I confiscate your phone and laptop?
- That's enough!

389
00:33:54,480 --> 00:33:56,560
He's 17 years old already.

390
00:33:58,080 --> 00:33:59,960
I hope we can be on the same page

391
00:34:00,040 --> 00:34:01,400
when it comes to educating our son.

392
00:34:01,480 --> 00:34:02,920
Is that too much to ask?

393
00:34:03,000 --> 00:34:04,720
Whose page are we talking about though?

394
00:34:04,800 --> 00:34:06,080
It's always yours.

395
00:34:06,160 --> 00:34:08,040
You're always in the right.
We're always in the wrong.

396
00:34:08,120 --> 00:34:09,239
Always?

397
00:34:09,320 --> 00:34:11,000
Can you treat me fairly?

398
00:34:11,520 --> 00:34:13,600
I've listened to you many times
and look at what has happened!

399
00:34:13,679 --> 00:34:16,000
It's clear that I'm always right!
However, I…

400
00:34:16,080 --> 00:34:17,560
Shanwen!

401
00:34:17,639 --> 00:34:19,040
Stop chasing after him!

402
00:34:19,679 --> 00:34:21,280
Stop pushing him further!

403
00:35:59,480 --> 00:36:00,440
Here.

404
00:36:00,960 --> 00:36:02,240
It's your favorite milk tea.

405
00:36:05,920 --> 00:36:07,640
I haven't liked milk tea for a long time.

406
00:36:11,040 --> 00:36:12,520
What do you like then?

407
00:36:42,600 --> 00:36:44,240
Why did Cindy look for you?

408
00:36:44,320 --> 00:36:45,640
Did you like her?

409
00:36:50,880 --> 00:36:52,240
You're like the rest of them.

410
00:36:52,760 --> 00:36:54,120
None of you believe me.

411
00:37:04,480 --> 00:37:05,720
Don't worry.

412
00:37:07,680 --> 00:37:09,520
I believe that you didn't kill anyone.

413
00:37:15,600 --> 00:37:16,960
Do you really believe me?

414
00:37:24,240 --> 00:37:26,720
How could my son do something like that?

415
00:37:30,160 --> 00:37:32,440
I'll do everything to protect you…

416
00:37:33,400 --> 00:37:34,440
and support you.

417
00:37:57,600 --> 00:37:58,760
Hurry up. We're going to be late.

418
00:38:03,960 --> 00:38:05,120
I'm not going.

419
00:38:08,640 --> 00:38:10,120
Don't be like this.

420
00:38:11,320 --> 00:38:13,600
I'm not in the mood
to put on an act with you tonight.

421
00:38:16,240 --> 00:38:18,360
You know that Dehui
is plotting to kick me out.

422
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:20,560
Tonight's dinner is very important to me.

423
00:38:21,480 --> 00:38:23,280
Our son is a murder suspect.

424
00:38:23,360 --> 00:38:24,960
How can you act as if nothing happened?

425
00:38:25,040 --> 00:38:27,320
He was only called in for questioning,

426
00:38:27,400 --> 00:38:29,560
and I believe Shanwen
wouldn't do something like that.

427
00:38:33,880 --> 00:38:35,520
It's been so many years.

428
00:38:35,600 --> 00:38:37,920
You should know how much
I've tolerated Dehui.

429
00:38:38,520 --> 00:38:39,800
I'm Zheng Shizhen's eldest son.

430
00:38:39,880 --> 00:38:42,800
He's the son of a mistress,
yet he has more authority than me!

431
00:38:44,640 --> 00:38:47,240
Many shareholders will be present tonight.
I need you there.

432
00:39:10,800 --> 00:39:14,160
LEAP DAY MURDER CASE - SUN SERA

433
00:41:16,280 --> 00:41:17,840
<i>Why did Cindy look for you?</i>

434
00:41:17,920 --> 00:41:19,000
<i>What did you tell the police?</i>

435
00:41:20,720 --> 00:41:22,520
<i>Why did Cindy look for you?</i>

436
00:41:23,480 --> 00:41:24,760
<i>Did you like her?</i>

437
00:41:26,920 --> 00:41:30,400
- <i>At 12:59 a.m. on March 5…</i>
- <i>Behind you!</i>

438
00:41:30,480 --> 00:41:32,720
<i>…Cindy called you. Why?</i>

439
00:41:42,200 --> 00:41:44,000
<i>Hello. It's Cindy.</i>

440
00:41:45,960 --> 00:41:47,040
What's the matter?

441
00:41:50,640 --> 00:41:51,760
What did you say?

442
00:42:06,760 --> 00:42:07,960
What's wrong?

443
00:42:08,520 --> 00:42:09,920
Go back to your room.

444
00:42:11,160 --> 00:42:12,600
Get off your high horse.

445
00:42:13,120 --> 00:42:15,200
Don't forget that I'm still your husband!

446
00:42:15,800 --> 00:42:17,040
Are you crazy?

447
00:42:17,120 --> 00:42:18,440
Go back to your room!

448
00:42:18,520 --> 00:42:21,520
What's wrong? The great artist
can't be touched by anyone?

449
00:42:23,120 --> 00:42:25,440
Is that so?
I didn't know you were such a tramp!

450
00:42:26,040 --> 00:42:29,360
- Come here!
- Let me go!

451
00:42:29,960 --> 00:42:31,040
- Let me go!
- Tell me!

452
00:42:31,120 --> 00:42:32,800
- Tell me!
- Shanwen!

453
00:42:32,880 --> 00:42:34,440
- Tell me!
- Shanwen!

454
00:42:34,520 --> 00:42:35,760
Shanwen!

455
00:43:11,760 --> 00:43:12,800
Get off!

456
00:43:15,560 --> 00:43:16,400
Shanwen!

457
00:43:18,320 --> 00:43:20,640
Shanwen!

458
00:43:22,400 --> 00:43:24,160
Shanwen!
